Steve:
>>
What I suggest
is that the Proposer be allowed to increase or decrease Priority
at a cost of 1 P-Note per unit change in Priority, but that for other
entities, the cost per unit change of Priority should be 3 P-Notes.
<<

At the moment one can increase the priority of other players'
proposals for a price of 1 P-note, and I don't see why this price
should be increased. And with the conservative spending habits of
Agorans I doubt that anyone would ever decrease a proposal's priority
if it costs 3 P-notes - if we want to have that kind of sponsoring
competition before proposals are distributed at all, why not make it
cheap and easy?

Kolja A.

